# Netlify SPA fallback
# ─────────────────────
# SvelteKit's `adapter-static` emits `build/index.html` as the SPA
# fallback. Netlify's static host serves files literally from the
# `publish` directory — without a rewrite rule, refreshing
# `https://example.com/remote/123` would 404 because there is no
# `build/remote/123/index.html` file. This rule rewrites every
# unmatched path to `/index.html` with status `200` so the client
# router takes over.
#
# Cloudflare Pages auto-emits its own `_redirects` in
# `build/_redirects`; the file under `static/` is harmless on
# Cloudflare (the build-time one wins) and required on Netlify.
# GitHub Pages does not honour `_redirects`; the SPA fallback is
# handled by 404.html — see `docs/hosting/github-pages.md`.
#
# Syntax: `<from>  <to>  <status>` (whitespace-separated, no quotes).
# `/*` matches every path; `200` is the Netlify-specific SPA
# fallback status (200, not 404, keeps the URL stable so the
# client router gets the path it expects).

/*    /index.html   200
